## INTRODUCTION

Purpose

This software design document describes the architecture and design of the frontend side of our Twitter Visualisation for crime data mobile application.

Scope

The frontend will handle the user interface and the interactions that occur in the application. It will consist of a cross-platform mobile application developed in React Native.

 It will include the following functionality:

- A home page with information about our Twitter Visualisation application.
- A page that displays crime related tweets with their crime type..
- A page that will show a map with trajectory models implemented into it.
- A visualisation page that will compare manually checked tweets to tweets checked by NLP
- It will be able to query the backend and display the retrieved data and a variety of relevant graphs.

## SYSTEM OVERVIEW

The frontend will show the user interface and the twitter data from the NODEJS backend. This data will then be displayed on the visualisation page, the crime tweets page and the track tweets page.

Architectural Design

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

The App.js file serves as the main entry point for the React Native application. There are routes which open the separate views, Visualisation.js, CrimeTweets.js, TrackTweets.js and Home.js. The initial route is set as Home.js, which is what the users will see when they first open the app.

Visualisation.js, CrimeTweets.js and TrackTweets.js fetch data from the backend NodeJS RESTful API.

Visualisation.js displays charts relating to tweet statistics, such as percentage of checked tweets against unchecked tweets and percentage of NLP-checked tweets against manually checked tweets.



## Design Rationale

We had three choices; use the frontend solution the previous team did, create a new application using React Native, or use NativeScript instead.

We didn&#39;t want to use to previous team&#39;s solution as their application was too broad compared to what we wanted to do, and to use it would mean we would have to learn how their solution worked as well as implement new features within it.

We then had to choose between React Native or NativeScript to build our cross-platform application.We chose React Native because NativeScript didn&#39;t have as much support and was more difficult to setup compared to React Native.

## HUMAN INTERFACE DESIGN

Overview

All primary user interactions with the software will be done through the frontend mobile phone application. The user will be able to view the tweets, either displayed on a map, or within a list. They will also be able to view trajectory models, as well as data from the NLP algorithm compared to expected data.

User Interface

## Home Screen

The home screen greets the user and give a description of the app and a brief description of all the different menu items.

## Crime Tweet List Page

The crime tweets page will show checked tweets that are related to crime. You can change the number of tweets shown, as well as filter for different types of crime.

## Crime Tweet Map Page

The tweet tracking page shows the user the location of different crime related tweets and once the trajectory mapping is integrated the pins that are related will be connected to show relation. You can also filter by the type of crime that tweet is related to.
